From 0d7840ef2873d800cc3a70d8d6b9a3cffc4d51b9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ren Wang <iamwrm@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 23:15:19 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Preserve streamed Responses text when terminal output is
 empty

ChatGPT Codex can emit response.output_text.delta frames while omitting
the assembled assistant message from the terminal response output. Grok
showed those deltas, then converted the empty terminal response to no
conversation items and retried it as no_visible_content.

Accumulate streamed text and synthesize/fill the final Assistant item only
when typed terminal output has no visible text. Also handle backends that
send only response.output_text.done, without duplicating normal deltas.
---
